ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Yes, I would recommend this course. Its very good for anyone wanting to understand or go into medical imaging.
Yes I would recommend this course.

The material is challenging- which is ok but be prepared for a lot of self-study. I think this class should only be taken if you have a need for imaging modalities in the context of research or the like.
Yeah I would definitely recommend this course especially to those who are interested to Imaging field.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: This course has given me a different perspective in the realm of engineering and as an electrical engineer some of the other fields I can apply myself in like bio-medical engineering discipline.
I certainly have a much better understanding of MR physics and CT. I hope to use these in the future

Before, I didn't know very much about other imaging modalities other than MRI. After this course I had a clear picture of the basic principles of other techniques. Lectures in MRI helped me to deepen my understanding in this area.
